# üõ†Ô∏è Installation Guide

This project uses **Jupyter Notebook** in an **Anaconda environment** to build a machine learning model that predicts Hansen Solubility Parameters (Œ¥d, Œ¥p, Œ¥h) using Lasso linear regression. It leverages cheminformatics and data science libraries such as RDKit, scikit-learn, pandas, and matplotlib.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Environment Setup

### 1. Install Anaconda

First, install Anaconda from the [official site](https://docs.anaconda.com/anaconda/install/).

---

### 2. Create and Activate a New Conda Environment with RDKit

Use the following command to create a dedicated environment:

conda create -c conda-forge -n hansen-ml-env rdkit

### 3.After installation of RDkit, activate the Rdkit environment using the following command

conda activate my-rdkit-env 
Within my-rdkit-env Install Scikit-learn

conda install scikit-learn  
Install Jupyternotebook 

conda install -c conda-forge notebook  
Install pytorch 

